args:
Despite defeating the soldiers, the party is
subjected to the interrogations of the Grams
Templars. But just as they are about to be
dragged away, a mysterious interloper ends the
situation without incident. This man turns
out to be Gatov, the sender of the letter.
Ha! Who's the whelp now, punks?\n...Say, you okay there, old timer?
Thank you ever so much, kind sir.\nIf I may, who are you people?
Just some do-gooders passin' through.\nNow get on in there while ya can!
Oh, no! I could never seek to go behind\nthe Church's back! I will continue to try\neverything I can to obtain permission.

Now then, Ranzal. Did we not VERY
recently have a conversation where I
advised you to refrain from engaging in
conspicuous behavior?
Sorry, but when I see somethin' like that,\nI ain't the type to sit around on my butt\ntwiddlin' my thumbs.
It would seem they caught wind\nof all the commotion.
What's the plan? We booking it?

If we ran now, it would make us look even
more suspicious. We've no choice but to
stay here and try to manage our way
through this.
We heard there were people here causing\nquite the ruckus. Was that you?
Who knows? Although there WAS some\nkinda brawl or whatnot happenin' earlier.
You are clearly not citizens of Grams,\nyet your dress suggests you are no mere\npeasants. Name yourselves, strangers.
Er, uh, nobody! Yep, that's us.\nWhooole buncha nobodies.
I asked for your identities,\nnot some cheap sidestep.
Oh, is THAT what you wanted?!\nWell then, I'm...ummm...

Oh, very well. I had hoped to act with as
much secrecy as possible, but there is
clearly no hiding the dignity that oozes
from my very pores.
Given the situation, I've no choice but to\nbe forthright and reveal my true self.
Good Templars, permit me to\nintroduce myself properly...
I am the chairwoman of the\nRose et Chaton Family Company.
Just so—and we have come here to stock\nour shelves with all manner of luxury\nGramsian specialties.

The goods here are of the highest quality,
and they fly off our shelves and straight
into the homes and hearts of many a
fine and noble customer!
Well, I suppose that makes sense.\nI'll see your permit, in that case.
That's right. If you're here to buy goods,\nyou will have been issued a commerce\npermit from the Church.
Oooooh, THAAAAT permit! Yes, of course.\nNow where did I put it...?
Surely a clever trader such as yourself\nwould have their permit near at hand, yes?
How very odd... I was sure I had it...
Oh, that's right! Silly me! I must have\nleft it at the cafe we stopped into earlier.

Enough of this foolishness! You people
clearly have no permit—you're merely
a gang of panicked fools attempting to
spin your way out of trouble.
Do I strike you as someone who panics,\nmy good sir?
Behold, the permit you so desired.\nFeel free to feast your eyes upon it\nuntil you are wholly satisfied.
Well, this...does appear to be authentic.

Of course it is! Who do you take us for?
Now then, if we may, we're off to the
marketplace to purchase our supplies.
Be well, good knights.
Heavens, but this is exhausting.\nWhat is it now?
Your answers are too slick for my taste.\nWe are taking you into custody so we\nmight examine the matter further.
But we possess a permit, my good man!\nYou have no reason to detain us.
And yet if you want to pass so badly,\nyou would know coin greases the way.\nSuch is the way of things here.
You're a bunch of underhanded jerks!
If you don't want any trouble,\nquiet down and obey. Otherwise...
Do you have some business with these\npeople, my good captain?
You! This has nothing to do with you.\nBegone from here at once!
I'm afraid I cannot do that.
The Rose et Chaton Family Company has\nsigned a contract with me to guard the\ntransportation of their goods.
So long as I have a contractual duty to\nprotect them, I cannot turn a blind eye\nto this unfortunate situation.
My my! It appears the mercenaries\nI hired have finally arrived.
If you're unhappy with the situation,\nthen let us consider neutrality and entrust\njudgment to our fine law enforcement.
Although in that event, I must inform them\nabout everything—including the fact you\nsought a bribe. Is this satisfactory?
You think yourself far too important,\nlittle man. I shall not forget this!
I can't believe you thought to arrange\nfor a trade permit in advance, Chelle.
And that you ALSO had the foresight\nto hire mercenaries for security!
While I did obtain a permit, I actually\nhave no memory of hiring mercenaries.
Then who the heck is this guy?!
I have no idea! I simply saw an opening\nand decided to play along.

Your reputation as a capable woman
precedes you, and I see it is well earned.
You are a true marvel at thinking on
your feet.
Wait, ya know us?! Does that mean...?
My apologies. I am the captain\nof Grams's 12th Division Watch.
You're the one who sent the letter\nto my brother Leonidas.
I am indeed. However, I would suggest\nwe save the finer points of this\nconversation for a later time.
Permit me to guide you someplace safer.\nCome with me, everyone.
